Channel4.uk.description: In Italy, two foodies prepare a vegan banquet. In Greece, a couple set out to kickstart their food tours business. And a Yorkshire entrepreneur faces some life-changing decisions. (S8 Ep29)

Channel4.uk.title: Find It, Fix It, Flog It
Channel4.uk.description: In Tiverton, the boys find a moped that brings back memories, and fight over a petrol gauge that Simon wants to upcycle into a clock. (S4 Ep16)

Channel4.uk.title: Countdown
Channel4.uk.description: Colin Murray, Rachel Riley and Susie Dent host, with Les Dennis in Dictionary Corner, as contestants race against the clock to pit their wits against vowels, consonants and numbers.

Channel4.uk.title: A Place in the Sun
Channel4.uk.description: Eileen from Birmingham wants the perfect holiday home on Spain's Mar Menor to take time out from her demanding job. Leah Charles-King shows her what £43.5k can buy.

Channel4.uk.title: Help! We Bought a Village
Channel4.uk.description: After a crisis in confidence, Paul and Yip visit Italy to see other village projects first-hand. And Justin and Mel unearth a hidden document from World War I. (S3 Ep4/30)

Channel4.uk.description: The new run continues. The week's final visit is to Marc and Matt's gastropub in Kent. The pair have been building expectations throughout the week - will their place live up to the hype?

Channel4.uk.description: In Cardiff, David hosts a vegan dining experience. Can he prove that you can have your cake and save the planet? (Ep4/5)

Channel4.uk.description: Sisters Ros and Elizabeth look for a magnifique place in Bergerac for £350k. Will a grand country home, picture-perfection or a place ticking boxes by the minute have the je ne sais quoi?

UAndDavejavu.uk.description: Weather: Richard takes on the worst of the British weather as he braves a hurricane in a wind tunnel to assess the best in gust-busting gadgetry with the help of comedian Tim Vine. S3 Ep1

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Gadget Man
UAndDavejavu.uk.description: Public Transport: Richard turns his attention to the noise, dirt and discomfort of public transport as Russell Howard joins him on London's Tube to assess the effectiveness of gadgets. S3 Ep2

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Special Ops: To Catch a Criminal
UAndDavejavu.uk.description: Operation Chatham: Raheem Sterling is one of a string of multi-millionaires targeted by a highly-organised burglary gang as Surrey Police race to stop the group behind the attacks. S3 Ep2

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Special Ops: Crime Squad UK
UAndDavejavu.uk.description: Britain's most talented detectives pursue two gunmen killers in Northamptonshire, distraction burglars in sleepy Kent, and a multi-million-pound footwear scam in Manchester. S1 Ep1

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Outback Pilots
UAndDavejavu.uk.description: Crop-dusting ace Dennis faces extreme low-level flying in a race to complete the biggest job of the year, and Trevor and his rookie aviators prepare to save tourists in a fierce storm. S1 Ep1

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Outback Pilots
UAndDavejavu.uk.description: Denis is faced with the biggest job of his career as his crop-dusting skills are put to the test, and Rescue 510 attempts a quick run to the hospital to save a snakebite victim. S1 Ep2

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Storage Hunters UK
UAndDavejavu.uk.description: Carmarthen: Auction anarchy in Wales, where the bidders hope to get rich quick by bagging valuable storage lots. It's cloak-and-dagger stuff as spying equipment is on offer. S4 Ep5

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Storage Hunters UK
UAndDavejavu.uk.description: Cardiff: Viewers of a sensitive disposition beware - one of today's lots has the bidders gagging! And why is Heavy D dressed as a ninja? The classic auction antics continue. S4 Ep6

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Storage Hunters UK
UAndDavejavu.uk.description: Scunthorpe: It's off to sunny Scunny for the nomadic bargain hunters who tussle for storage lots. Barry and Darren try strong-arm tactics. Linda goes gaga over one auction. S4 Ep7

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Storage Hunters UK
UAndDavejavu.uk.description: Buckinghamshire: 'Lots' to play for in the auction-packed reality show. Heavy D and Sam team up, while Charlotte and Shaun have a father-daughter tiff of nuclear proportions. S4 Ep8

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Extreme Salvage Squad
UAndDavejavu.uk.description: Team Salvage head to the Northern Territory for an epic time-critical beach recovery, and Team Edge suffers a major cost blow-out on a job at Mount Disappointment. S4 Ep6

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Top Gear
UAndDavejavu.uk.description: Ciao! Jeremy Clarkson, Richard Hammond and James May travel to Italy for a series of challenges and increasingly loud arguments. Geordie randomist Ross Noble guests. S17 Ep2

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Top Gear

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Hairy Bikers' Best of British

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Rick Stein: From Venice to Istanbul

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Would I Lie To You?

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Richard Osman's House of Games

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Left Behind: Flanders loses his job and comes to work with Homer at the power plant. Homer prays for him to be fired. (S29 Ep19/21)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Throw Grampa from the Dane: The Simpsons visit Denmark and all fall in love with it - except Homer. Meanwhile, Grampa needs a serious operation. (S29 Ep20/21)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Novelization Correlation: Amy appears on the Professor Proton show. Penny hates the idea that the female protagonist in Leonard's novel is based on her. (S11 Ep15)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Neonatal Nomenclature: Bernadette's friends try various tactics to help her go into labour. (S11 Ep16)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Athenaeum Allocation: Leonard jumps through hoops to secure the perfect wedding venue for Sheldon and Amy. Howard and Bernadette face a big decision. (S11 Ep17)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Gates Excitation: The guys do everything in their power to meet Bill Gates when his firm has dealings with the pharmaceutical company Penny works for. (S11 Ep18)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: G.I. (Annoyed Grunt): Homer accidentally signs up for basic training in the army. And Marge and Grampa get roped in when they try to get him released. (S18 Ep5/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Moe 'n' a Lisa: Lisa discovers Moe's poetic talent and helps get him published. And he's so successful that he - and the Simpsons - are invited to a literary conference. (S18 Ep6/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Four Great Women and a Manicure: On a visit to the nail salon, Marge and Lisa discuss whether a woman can be simultaneously clever, powerful and beautiful. (S20 Ep20/21)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Man Who Came to Be Dinner: A new amusement park ride transports the Simpsons to Kang and Kodos's home planet, where they're held captive in a zoo. (S26 Ep10/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Supercruising: Life at Sea
E4Plus1.uk.description: On the North Africa and Europe voyage, the chefs prepare a fine-dining experience with a difference, while the Caribbean cruisers enjoy tranquil bamboo rafting in the scorching heat. (Ep4)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Oblivion
E4Plus1.uk.description: (2013) Sci-fi action-mystery set on a war-ravaged planet Earth that's been largely abandoned by humanity. With Tom Cruise, Andrea Riseborough, Olga Kurylenko and Morgan Freeman.

Film4.uk.title: The Green Mile
Film4.uk.description: (1999) Drama with Tom Hanks and Michael Clarke Duncan. Strange events occur when a man convicted of raping and murdering two young girls arrives on death row in a Louisiana prison.

Film4.uk.title: Open Range

Film4.uk.title: Roman Holiday
Film4.uk.description: (1953) Audrey Hepburn won her only Oscar in this romance as a bored princess who runs away from her duties and meets an American journalist (Gregory Peck), who shows her Rome.

Film4.uk.title: Bridge of Spies Interview Special
Film4.uk.description: Director Steven Spielberg and stars Tom Hanks and Mark Rylance talk about making their Cold War espionage drama.

Film4.uk.title: Storm over the Nile

Film4.uk.title: Bridge of Spies Interview Special
Film4.uk.description: Director Steven Spielberg and stars Tom Hanks and Mark Rylance talk about making their Cold War espionage drama.

Film4.uk.title: Bridge of Spies
Film4.uk.description: (2015) Tom Hanks and Mark Rylance star in Steven Spielberg's Cold War spy drama. After gaining notoriety for defending a Soviet spy, a US lawyer then tries to free a CIA pilot.

Film4.uk.title: Bullet Train
Film4.uk.description: (2022) Leaving from Platform 4 - a high octane, Shinkansen-set comedy thriller with Brad Pitt, Joey King and Michael Shannon. A jaded assassin does one last job on a villain-packed train.

Film4.uk.title: We're All Going to the World's...
Film4.uk.description: ...Fair: (2021) Jane Schoenbrun's creepy, freaky, coming-of-age horror starring Anna Cobb. A lonely teenage girl gets increasingly sucked into the unnerving nether-world of an online game.

Film4.uk.title: Kill List
Film4.uk.description: (2011) Horror. Neil Maskell and Michael Smiley star as friends whose latest job leads them into shockingly brutal, gory violence. With MyAnna Buring and Emma Fryer.

Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.title: Man in the Saddle
Film4.uk.description: (1951) Western. Randolph Scott stars as a rancher who's the target of unwelcome harassment by his richer and more powerful neighbour. With Alexander Knox, Joan Leslie and Ellen Drew.

Film4.uk.title: San Demetrio, London
Film4.uk.description: (1943) Fact-based drama about a group of Merchant Navy sailors who brave fire and the ocean to save the San Demetrio oil tanker after it's almost destroyed by a German cruiser.

Film4.uk.title: Three Hours to Kill
Film4.uk.description: (1954) Western starring Dana Andrews. A man falsely accused of murder gets a last-minute reprieve from the lynch mob so he can track down the real culprit.

Film4.uk.title: The Art of Racing in the Rain
Film4.uk.description: (2019) Touching comedy-drama. An ageing golden retriever (voiced by Kevin Costner) tells the story of his life with his best pal, a budding Formula 1 driver.

Film4.uk.title: Hidden Figures
Film4.uk.description: (2016) Taraji P. Henson, Octavia Spencer and Janelle Monáe star in the Oscar-nominated, fact-based drama about three women whose genius made a significant contribution to the space race.

Film4.uk.title: Bloodshot
Film4.uk.description: (2020) Vin Diesel stars in this action-packed superhero adventure. After he and his wife are killed, a US soldier is brought back to life and given superhuman powers.

Film4.uk.title: Venom
Film4.uk.description: (2018) Dark sci-fi action with Tom Hardy as Marvel's anti-hero. A reporter becomes inhabited by a ferocious extraterrestrial that has its own ideas on how to behave. With Michelle Williams.

Film4.uk.title: Saint Maud
Film4.uk.description: (2019) Psychological horror. After failing to save a life, a nurse transforms her life and vows to save the godless soul of a terminally-ill atheist woman from an eternity with Satan.

Film4.uk.title: The Enemy Below
Film4.uk.description: (1957) Second World War thriller. Robert Mitchum stars as the captain of a US destroyer in the North Atlantic hunting down a German U-boat and its world-weary captain, Curt Jurgens.

Film4.uk.title: River of No Return
Film4.uk.description: (1954) Western with Robert Mitchum and Marilyn Monroe. An ex-con and a saloon singer steer a raft through hostile territory to face a showdown with her crooked fiancé. With Rory Calhoun.

Film4.uk.title: Bridge of Spies Interview Special
Film4.uk.description: Director Steven Spielberg and stars Tom Hanks and Mark Rylance talk about making their Cold War espionage drama.

Film4.uk.description: (1984) Comedy action adventure starring Michael Douglas and Kathleen Turner. An adventurer helps a bestselling author to search for her sister, who's been kidnapped in Colombia.

Film4.uk.title: Angel Has Fallen
Film4.uk.description: (2019) Action-thriller sequel. Secret agent Mike Banning (Gerard Butler) goes on the run when he's framed for an attack on the President. Can he clear his name?

Film4.uk.title: X

GBNews.uk.title: Patrick Christys Tonight
